  "prompt": "What are probing question that you will ask to the user for buying an AC?",
  "response": "When helping a user decide on buying an air conditioner (AC), probing questions can help narrow down options and identify their specific needs. Here are some effective questions to consider:\n\n1. **Space Requirements**\n   - What size is the room or area where you plan to install the AC?\n   - Do you need an AC for a single room or for multiple rooms/home?\n\n2. **Usage and Purpose**\n   - How often do you plan to use the AC?\n   - Are you looking for cooling only, or do you also want heating options?\n\n3. **Type of AC**\n   - Have you considered which type of AC you prefer, such as a window unit, split unit, portable, or central air system?\n   - Do you have any brand preferences based on previous experiences?\n\n4. **Efficiency and Budget**\n   - What is your budget for purchasing an AC?\n   - Are you interested in energy-efficient models to save on electricity bills?\n\n5. **Installation and Maintenance**\n   - Do you have existing ductwork if you're considering a central system?\n   - Are you comfortable with DIY installation, or would you prefer professional installation?\n\n6. **Features and Technology**\n   - Are there specific features that are important to you, such as smart technology, programmable settings, or air purification?\n   - How important is noise level for you? Do you require a particularly quiet model?\n\n7. **Climate and Environment**\n   - What is the climate like in your area? Does it get very hot and humid?\n   - Have you experienced any issues with your current cooling system that you\u2019d like to address?\n\n8. **Health and Allergies**\n   - Are there any allergies or health concerns that might influence your choice of air conditioning, such as the need for better air filtration?\n\n9. **Future Considerations**\n   - Are you planning any renovations or changes to your living space that might affect your choice?\n   - How long do you anticipate staying in your current home?\n\nThese questions will help you gather important information to recommend the most suitable air conditioning options for the user.",
